name: Pink Flannel Flower
description:
A rare Australian plant, the Pink Flannel Flower only blooms in very specific conditions. The seeds can lay dormant for years on end, waiting for a special confluence of events forming the right conditions for their emergence – a year or so after bushfire followed by rainfall. These special flowers covered our land a year after the Black Summer. They provide a ray of hope and their Flower Essence helps with healing the emotional trauma from experiencing wild fire.

Photo taken early 2021
